	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Hardware stores?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />What we need are some links to good places to buy hardware. Compare to the Nintendo DS scene, where the <a href="http://www.dev-scene.com/NDS_Homebrew_FAQ#What_do_I_need_to_run_Homebrew.3F" class="postlink">required hardware</a> is pretty much nailed down. As far as I know, it would be a good idea to list stores and ballpark prices for the following:
<br /><ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>UNROM or UOROM compatible NES cart PCBs with a socket for a PRG flash chip (<a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=16833#16833" class="postlink">Memblers says they run about 20 USD assembled</a>) </li><li>flash chips to put into these PCBs </li><li>flash programmers to write to the flash chips </li><li>GameBit screwdrivers to open your carts and replace the PCB </li><li>Anything needed to open the NES itself and mod-chip it (that is, cut pin 4) </li></ol>
<br />Once we have all these pieces in place, then we can make a step-by-step guide to getting started with NES development.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


